The paper deals with the problem of packing items into bins, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The specific problem of packing hypercubes into bins involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.CC). Lastly, the paper also discusses the use of algorithms and their analysis, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT).
